<h1 class="doc-page-title">Reporting</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">COMPASS provides comprehensive reporting capabilities for product governance, performance metrics, and compliance tracking.</p>

<h2 id="overview">Reporting overview</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS reporting is organised into several categories:</p>

                <div class="row mt-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt text-danger"></i> RAID reports</h3>
                                <p class="small">Comprehensive reports on risks, actions, issues, and milestones with filtering and analysis capabilities.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-chart-line text-success"></i> Performance reports</h3>
                                <p class="small">Product and enterprise performance metrics with historical trends and target tracking.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check text-info"></i> Compliance reports</h3>
                                <p class="small">Functional standards assessments and compliance tracking across products and standards.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-dashboard text-primary"></i> Dashboards</h3>
                                <p class="small">Interactive dashboards providing at-a-glance views of key metrics and RAID status.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="raid-reports">RAID reports</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risks and issues report</h3>
                <p>The primary RAID report provides a comprehensive table-based view of all risks and issues.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Features:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Comprehensive data:</strong> Shows all key fields for risks and issues</li>
                    <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Click any column header to sort</li>
                    <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Filter by product, status, owner, date range, and more</li>
                    <li><strong>Search:</strong> Full-text search across all fields</li>
                    <li><strong>Pagination:</strong> Navigate through large datasets</li>
                    <li><strong>Export:</strong> Download to Excel, PDF, or CSV</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Available filters:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Product:</strong> Filter by one or more products</li>
                    <li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by current status</li>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Filter risks by risk type</li>
                    <li><strong>Tier:</strong> Filter risks by tier level</li>
                    <li><strong>Owner:</strong> Filter by assigned owner</li>
                    <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Filter issues by priority level</li>
                    <li><strong>Date range:</strong> Filter by created date or target date</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk score:</strong> Filter risks by score range</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><strong>Tip:</strong> Save your frequently used filter combinations as personalised report views.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Analysis report</h3>
                <p>The analysis report provides visual insights into RAID data through charts and graphs.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Available analyses:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk distribution:</strong> Breakdown of risks by type, tier, and status</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk heat map:</strong> Visual representation of risks by impact and likelihood</li>
                    <li><strong>Issue status:</strong> Current state of all issues</li>
                    <li><strong>Action completion:</strong> Progress on actions by status and source</li>
                    <li><strong>Trend analysis:</strong> Changes in RAID items over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Product comparison:</strong> Compare RAID metrics across products</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Action tracking report</h3>
                <p>Dedicated report for monitoring actions and their completion.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Key metrics:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Total actions by status</li>
                    <li>Overdue actions</li>
                    <li>Actions due soon (next 7/14/30 days)</li>
                    <li>Completion rate by owner</li>
                    <li>Actions by source type</li>
                    <li>Average time to completion</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Milestone status report</h3>
                <p>Track milestone progress and identify at-risk deliverables.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Report includes:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Upcoming milestones</li>
                    <li>Milestones at risk or delayed</li>
                    <li>Recently achieved milestones</li>
                    <li>Associated RAID items per milestone</li>
                    <li>Timeline visualisation</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="performance">Performance reporting</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product performance metrics</h3>
                <p>Track and visualise performance metrics for individual products.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Features:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Current values:</strong> Latest submitted metric values</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical trends:</strong> Line charts showing performance over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Target comparison:</strong> Actual vs. target performance</li>
                    <li><strong>Period selection:</strong> View data by week, month, quarter, or year</li>
                    <li><strong>Multi-metric view:</strong> Compare multiple metrics on one chart</li>
                    <li><strong>Data table:</strong> Tabular view of historical submissions</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Available metric types:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Service availability and uptime</li>
                    <li>User satisfaction scores</li>
                    <li>Transaction volumes</li>
                    <li>Response times</li>
                    <li>Error rates</li>
                    <li>Cost per transaction</li>
                    <li>Percentage-based metrics (0-100%)</li>
                    <li>Custom product-specific metrics</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Performance metric submission history</h3>
                <p>View the complete history of metric submissions for audit and analysis.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Information shown:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Submission date and time</li>
                    <li>Submitted by (user)</li>
                    <li>Metric values</li>
                    <li>Associated commentary or notes</li>
                    <li>Period covered</li>
                    <li>Changes from previous submission</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="enterprise">Enterprise reporting</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics dashboard</h3>
                <p>High-level view of enterprise-wide KPIs and strategic metrics.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Dashboard sections:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Strategic objectives:</strong> Progress towards strategic goals</li>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio health:</strong> Overall health indicators across all products</li>
                    <li><strong>Resource utilisation:</strong> Budget, staff, and capacity metrics</li>
                    <li><strong>Compliance status:</strong> Overall compliance with standards and policies</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk exposure:</strong> Enterprise-level risk profile</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Functional standards compliance</h3>
                <p>Track compliance with DDaT functional standards across the product portfolio.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Reports include:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Compliance summary:</strong> Overall compliance levels by standard</li>
                    <li><strong>Assessment history:</strong> Tracking compliance progress over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Gap analysis:</strong> Areas of non-compliance requiring attention</li>
                    <li><strong>Product comparison:</strong> Compare compliance across products</li>
                    <li><strong>Practice area breakdown:</strong> Compliance by practice area and theme</li>
                    <li><strong>Evidence repository:</strong> Supporting evidence for assessments</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Portfolio analysis</h3>
                <p>Comprehensive analysis across the entire product portfolio.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Analysis views:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Product lifecycle distribution</li>
                    <li>Investment allocation</li>
                    <li>Strategic alignment</li>
                    <li>Risk and issue concentrations</li>
                    <li>Performance benchmarking</li>
                    <li>Resource distribution</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="dashboards">Dashboards</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Home dashboard</h3>
                <p>The COMPASS home dashboard provides a personalised, filterable view of all items assigned to or owned by you.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Dashboard tabs:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Summary cards showing counts across all item types with colour-coded status indicators</li>
                    <li><strong>Products:</strong> Products where you are a contact, with RAID item counts and quick-access buttons</li>
                    <li><strong>Issues:</strong> All issues you own with filtering by status, severity, and time period</li>
                    <li><strong>Risks:</strong> All risks you own with filtering by status, risk score, and time period</li>
                    <li><strong>Actions:</strong> All actions assigned to you with filtering by status, priority, and time period</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestones:</strong> All milestones you own with progress tracking and filtering</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Dashboard features:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Priority items section:</strong> Automatically surfaces overdue items, critical issues, and high-priority actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestones progress bar:</strong> Visual representation of milestone completion across all your milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Overdue indicators:</strong> Red badges and icons highlight items requiring immediate attention</li>
                    <li><strong>Urgent indicators:</strong> Amber warnings for items due within 7 days</li>
                    <li><strong>Inline filters:</strong> Always-visible filter bar for instant view refinement</li>
                    <li><strong>Dynamic counts:</strong> Badge counts update based on filtered results</li>
                    <li><strong>Quick actions:</strong> Direct links to edit items without leaving the dashboard</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product dashboard</h3>
                <p>Comprehensive view of a single product's status and health.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Dashboard sections:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Product information:</strong> Key details, contacts, and status</li>
                    <li><strong>RAID summary:</strong> Count and status of all RAID items</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk heat map:</strong> Visual representation of product risks</li>
                    <li><strong>Recent issues:</strong> Latest issues requiring attention</li>
                    <li><strong>Action status:</strong> Progress on product actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone timeline:</strong> Upcoming and recent milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Operational reports:</strong> Key metrics and trends</li>
                    <li><strong>Compliance status:</strong> Standards assessment results</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Executive dashboard</h3>
                <p>High-level strategic view for senior leadership.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Executive metrics:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Enterprise risk profile</li>
                    <li>Portfolio health indicators</li>
                    <li>Strategic objective progress</li>
                    <li>Critical issues requiring escalation</li>
                    <li>Budget and resource status</li>
                    <li>Compliance summary</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="export">Exporting data</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Export formats</h3>
                
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-file-excel text-success"></i> Excel (.xlsx)</h4>
                                <p class="small">Full data export with formatting, suitable for further analysis in Excel.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf text-danger"></i> PDF</h4>
                                <p class="small">Print-ready formatted report suitable for distribution and archiving.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-file-csv text-info"></i> CSV</h4>
                                <p class="small">Raw data export compatible with most systems and tools.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Export options</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Current page:</strong> Export only the data visible on the current page</li>
                    <li><strong>All pages:</strong> Export all data matching current filters</li>
                    <li><strong>Selected items:</strong> Export only selected rows</li>
                    <li><strong>Include charts:</strong> Include visualisations in PDF exports</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Scheduled exports</h3>
                <p>Configure automatic report generation and delivery.</p>

                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">Schedule options:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> Daily, weekly, monthly, or quarterly</li>
                    <li><strong>Format:</strong> Select export format</li>
                    <li><strong>Recipients:</strong> Email recipients for delivery</li>
                    <li><strong>Filters:</strong> Save filter configuration with schedule</li>
                    <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Choose specific day/time for generation</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Report customisation</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Personalised views</h3>
                <p>Save frequently used report configurations:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Save filter combinations</li>
                    <li>Save column visibility settings</li>
                    <li>Save sort preferences</li>
                    <li>Give views meaningful names</li>
                    <li>Share views with team members</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Column customisation</h3>
                <p>Most reports allow you to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Show or hide columns</li>
                    <li>Reorder columns by dragging</li>
                    <li>Resize columns</li>
                    <li>Group by specific columns</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Date range selection</h3>
                <p>Flexible date filtering options:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Last 7/14/30/90 days</li>
                    <li>This/last week/month/quarter/year</li>
                    <li>Custom date range</li>
                    <li>Relative dates (e.g., "due in next 14 days")</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Best practices for reporting</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data quality</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensure RAID items are kept up to date</li>
                    <li>Use consistent naming conventions</li>
                    <li>Complete all required fields for meaningful reports</li>
                    <li>Regular data quality reviews</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Report usage</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Choose the right report for your audience</li>
                    <li>Use filters to focus on relevant data</li>
                    <li>Export and share reports regularly with stakeholders</li>
                    <li>Review trends over time, not just snapshots</li>
                    <li>Combine multiple reports for comprehensive analysis</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Performance considerations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use filters to reduce dataset size for faster loading</li>
                    <li>Schedule large exports during off-peak hours</li>
                    <li>Save commonly used views rather than re-filtering each time</li>
                    <li>Export to Excel for complex analysis rather than browser-based sorting</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-primary mt-4">
                    <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Need help?</h3>
                    <p class="mb-2">For more information about reporting:</p>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><a href="@Url.Action("UserGuide", "Documentation")">User guide</a> - Step-by-step instructions for viewing reports</li>
                        <li><a href="@Url.Action("RaidManagement", "Documentation")">Product governance</a> - Understanding the data in RAID reports</li>
                        <li>Contact support for assistance with custom reports</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

